08/11/2009
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The Health Ministry announced on Friday (November 6th) a swine flu epidemic in the country.
So far, the virus has killed six people.
All schools in the country will be closed as of Monday.
Hospitals have suspended medical checks of children and pregnant women.
Cinemas, theatres and other public sites have not been ordered to close, but people have been advised to avoid crowds.
Bulgaria suffers a shortage of swine flu medication and has called on other EU member states and pharmaceutical companies to help.
(Dnevnik, bTV, BTA, Makfax - 06/11/09)
